For the “naive” and “impenitent” man, the world is a neutral space
where one chooses agreeable situations while believing it possible to
avoid the disagreeable, given a certain cleverness and luck. Quite
evidently, the man who is unaware that existence is an immense
furnace, has no imperious reason for wishing to leave it.
